ANC spokesperson, Pule Mabe, has weighed in on allegations against Health Minister, Zweli Mkhize. He says South Africans should take comfort in knowing the matter is being discussed and probed. Mkhize is accused of benefitting from a communications tender awarded to his close associates at Digital Vibes. The latest allegation is that Digital Vibes bought a Land Cruiser for Mkhize’s son. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - ANC spokesperson Pule Mabe has weighed in on allegations against Health Minister, Zweli Mkhize. He says South Africans should take comfort in knowing the matter is being discussed and probed. Mkhize is accused of benefitting from a communications tender awarded to his close associates at Digital Vibes. READ: Ramaphosa describes allegations against Mkhize as serious, disturbing The latest allegation is that Digital Vibes bought a Land Cruiser for Mkhize's son. Mkhize denies any wrongdoing. "The comfort that we should have is that the president said that conversation is taking place. That should be saying to all South Africans that we are paying attention to that issue," Mabe said.